<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="319" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/40363/6</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-09">July 9,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>I thank you for your memorandum number 308 of July 5th,<note n="90" xml:id="d319fn90">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_322">p. 322</ref>.</note>
                        by which you have forwarded to me a recommended message to the Prime
                        Minister in response to his 339.</p>
                    <p>I have sent the message and I request that you initiate the measures listed
                        in the fourth paragraph of your memorandum.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps">oosevelt</hi>]</signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>